---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '../../components/Breadcrumbs.astro';
import CTABlock from '../../components/CTABlock.astro';
import BlogHero from '../../components/BlogHero.astro';
import BlogFigure from '../../components/BlogFigure.astro';
import RelatedPosts from '../../components/RelatedPosts.astro';
import { business, BASE } from '../../data/business';
import { postBySlug, postsBySlugs, RELATED_POSTS } from '../../data/posts';

const post = postBySlug('led-exterior-floodlight-sorn')!;
const relatedPosts = postsBySlugs(RELATED_POSTS[post.slug] ?? []).slice(0, 3);
const siteUrl = business.siteUrl.replace(/\/$/, '');
const url = `${siteUrl}/blog/${post.slug}/`;
const ogImage = `${siteUrl}${BASE}/gallery/sorn-led-exterior-floodlight-06-1600w.jpg`;

const articleSchema = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'Article',
  '@id': `${url}#article`,
  headline: post.title,
  description: post.description,
  inLanguage: 'en-GB',
  datePublished: post.date,
  dateModified: post.date,
  author: { '@type': 'Person', name: post.author, worksFor: { '@id': `${siteUrl}/#business` } },
  publisher: { '@id': `${siteUrl}/#business` },
  image: [ogImage],
  mainEntityOfPage: url,
  keywords: [post.keyword],
  wordCount: post.wordCount,
};
---
<BaseLayout
  title={`${post.title} | Sorn Handyman Services`}
  description={post.description}
  canonicalPath={`/blog/${post.slug}/`}
  ogImage={ogImage}
  ogType="article"
  extraSchema={articleSchema}
>
  <Breadcrumbs trail={[
    { name: 'Home', href: `${BASE}/` },
    { name: 'Blog', href: `${BASE}/blog/` },
    { name: post.title },
  ]} />

  <article class="container-x py-10 lg:py-14 max-w-3xl">
    <header>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-2 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-amber-600">
        <span>{post.area}</span>
        <span aria-hidden class="text-navy-900/20">·</span>
        <span class="text-navy-900/60">{post.readMinutes} min read</span>
        <span aria-hidden class="text-navy-900/20">·</span>
        <time datetime={post.date} class="text-navy-900/60">{post.dateDisplay}</time>
      </div>
      <h1 class="mt-4 font-serif text-4xl md:text-5xl font-black text-navy-900 leading-tight">
        {post.title}
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-5 text-lg text-navy-900/75">
        An LED exterior floodlight fitted for a new customer in Sorn. Bright,
        efficient and neatly wired back to the existing external circuit.
      </p>
    </header>

    <BlogHero slug="sorn-led-exterior-floodlight-06" />

    <div class="prose-sorn mt-8 text-lg cv-auto">
      <h2>What the job involved</h2>
      <p>
        The mounting position was set to give the customer the coverage they
        wanted at the door and up the drive without glare into the window or
        across to the neighbours. Fixings went into sound masonry and the
        cable route was planned before we broke any surface.
      </p>
      <p>
        Supply came off the existing external circuit, run in weatherproof
        cable back to the light with a proper junction. The fitting was levelled,
        tested under power, and the beam aimed before we finished up.
      </p>

      <BlogFigure slug="sorn-led-exterior-floodlight-06" />

      <h2>Things to think about before you start</h2>
      <p>
        Pick the spot carefully. A flood that lights up the drive can also
        blast straight through your neighbour's bedroom window — angle and
        cut-off matter as much as lumens. Shielded fittings and movement
        sensors keep the light where you want it.
      </p>
      <p>
        Exterior electrics must be right. Weatherproof glands, the correct
        cable rating for outdoor use, and a proper earth path back to the
        consumer unit are all non-negotiable. Adding a floodlight off an
        unsuitable indoor circuit is a fault waiting to happen.
      </p>

      <p>
        If you are in Sorn and need something similar, Fraser will come and
        look for free. Call <strong>07900 255876</strong> or WhatsApp
        <strong>+44 7472 223323</strong>. FREE no-obligation quote, every job
        priced individually.
      </p>

      <div class="not-prose mt-10 rounded-2xl border border-navy-900/10 bg-navy-50/50 p-6">
        <p class="text-sm text-navy-900/60">Written by</p>
        <p class="mt-1 font-serif text-xl font-bold text-navy-900">{post.author}</p>
        <p class="mt-2 text-navy-900/75 text-sm">{post.authorBio}</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>

  {relatedPosts.length > 0 && (
    <RelatedPosts posts={relatedPosts} eyebrow="Keep reading" heading="Related posts" variant="tinted" />
  )}

  <CTABlock
    heading="Dark corner of the garden or drive?"
    sub="Send a photo and we will tell you what fitting would suit."
    location="Sorn"
  />
</BaseLayout>
